msgid "34. Kāṇamātusikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on Kāṇamātu"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.79"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.34.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.34.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.321"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa743"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kāṇamātā upāsikā saddhā hoti pasannā."
msgstr ""
"At that  time there was a female lay follower Kāṇamātā who had faith and "
"confidence."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Kāṇā gāmake aññatarassa purisassa dinnā hoti."
msgstr ""
"She had a daughter, Kāṇā, who had been given in marriage to a man in a "
"certain village."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇā mātugharaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr "On one occasion Kāṇā went to her mother’s house on some business."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "Kāṇā’s husband sent her a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "“āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgatan”ti."
msgstr "“Please come Kāṇā; I want you back.”"

#. VAR: pūvaṃ → pūpaṃ (ṇvādi­mog­gallāne)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā “kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantun”ti pūvaṃ paci."
msgstr ""
"Kāṇamātā thought, “It’s shameful to go empty-handed,” and she baked biscuits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Just when the biscuits were finished, a monk who was an alms-collector "
"entered Kāṇamātā’s house,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and she gave him biscuits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr "After leaving, he told another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and he too was given biscuits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "And the same happened a third time."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.322"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "At that, all the biscuits were gone."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa744"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa745"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr ""
"A second time Kāṇā’s husband sent her the same message, and everything "
"unfolded as before."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "“āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgatan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho kāṇamātā upāsikā “kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantun”ti pūvaṃ "
"paci."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid ""
"Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid "Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid "Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "A third time he sent the same message,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid "“āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.26"
msgid "Sace kāṇā nāgacchissati, ahaṃ aññaṃ pajāpatiṃ ānessāmī”ti."
msgstr "adding, “If Kāṇā doesn’t come, I’ll find another wife.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.27"
msgid ""
"Tatiyampi kho kāṇamātā upāsikā kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantunti pūvaṃ paci."
msgstr "But once again all the biscuits were given to monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.28"
msgid ""
"Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.29"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.30"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.31"
msgid "Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.32"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.33"
msgid "Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.34"
msgid "Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.35"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇāya sāmiko aññaṃ pajāpatiṃ ānesi."
msgstr "Kāṇā’s husband found another wife,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa746"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.36"
msgid "Assosi kho kāṇā—“tena kira purisena aññā pajāpati ānītā”ti."
msgstr "and when Kāṇā heard what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.37"
msgid "Sā rodantī aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "she cried."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.38"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kāṇamātāya "
"upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards the Master robed up in the morning, took his bowl and robe, "
"and went to Kāṇamātā’s house,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.39"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.40"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Kāṇamātā approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.41"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.42"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho kāṇamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ bhagavā etadavoca—“kissāyaṃ kāṇā "
"rodatī”ti?"
msgstr "The Master asked her why Kāṇā was crying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.43"
msgid "Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "and she told him what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.1.44"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā kāṇamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā "
"samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"After instructing, inspiring, and gladdening her with a teaching, the Master "
"rose from his seat and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.80"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.34.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa747"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro sattho rājagahā paṭiyālokaṃ gantukāmo hoti."
msgstr ""
"Around the same time a certain caravan was ready to go south from Rājagaha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu taṃ satthaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"A monk who was an alms-collector approached that caravan to get almsfood,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.323"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Aññataro upāsako tassa bhikkhuno sattuṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and a lay follower gave him barley-meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr "After leaving, that monk told another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "Tassapi sattuṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and he too was given barley-meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi sattuṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "And the same happened a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pātheyyaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "At that, all the barley-meal was gone."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho so upāsako te manusse etadavoca—"
msgstr "That lay follower said to the other people in the caravan,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "“ajjaṇho, ayyā, āgametha, yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pātheyyaṃ ayyānaṃ dinnaṃ."
msgstr "“Sirs, please wait one day. I have given my provisions to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "Pātheyyaṃ paṭiyādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "and I need to prepare more provisions.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Nāyyo → nāyya (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid "“Nāyyo sakkā āgametuṃ, payāto sattho”ti agamaṃsu."
msgstr "“We can’t wait; the caravan is going already.” And they departed."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tassa upāsakassa pātheyyaṃ paṭiyādetvā pacchā gacchantassa corā "
"acchindiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"After preparing provisions, that lay follower followed after the caravan, "
"but he was robbed by thieves."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā paṭiggahessanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics receive without moderation?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ imesaṃ datvā pacchā gacchanto corehi acchinno”ti."
msgstr ""
"This man gave to them, and then because he was following after the caravan "
"he was robbed by thieves.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa748"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid ""
"“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase "
"paṭicca—"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten "
"reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "saṃghasuṭṭhutāya, saṃghaphāsutāya … pe … vinayānuggahāya."
msgstr ""
"for the well-being of the Order, for the comfort of the Order, for the "
"restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the "
"restraint of corruptions in the present life, for avoiding corruptions in "
"future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase "
"the confidence of those who have it, for the continuation of the true "
"Teaching, and for supporting the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.21a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa749"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.324"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: paṭiggaṇheyya → paṭigaṇheyya (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid ""
"“Bhikkhuṃ paneva kulaṃ upagataṃ pūvehi vā manthehi vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyya, "
"ākaṅkhamānena bhikkhunā dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahetabbā tato ce uttari "
"paṭiggaṇheyya pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk approaches a family and is invited to take biscuits or cereals, "
"he may accept two or three bowlfuls if he wishes. If he accepts more than "
"that, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.23"
msgid ""
"Dvattipattapūre paṭiggahetvā tato nīharitvā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ "
"saṃvibhajitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he accepts two or three bowlfuls, he should take it away and share it "
"with the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.24"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti."
msgstr "This is the proper procedure.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs1.2.25"
msgid "(<em>34</em>:<strong>83</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.34.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.34.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa750"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva kulaṃ upagatanti"
msgstr "A monk approaches a family:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "kulaṃ nāma cattāri kulāni—"
msgstr "there are four kinds of families:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ."
msgstr ""
"aristocratic families, brahmin families, merchant families, worker families."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa751"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "Upagatanti"
msgstr "Approaches:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "tattha gataṃ."
msgstr "he has gone there."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa752"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Pūvaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Biscuits:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci paheṇakatthāya paṭiyattaṃ."
msgstr "whatever has been prepared for the purpose of sending away."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa753"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Manthaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Cereals:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci pātheyyatthāya paṭiyattaṃ."
msgstr "whatever has been prepared as provisions for a journey."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa754"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyāti"
msgstr "Is invited to take:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ icchasi tāvatakaṃ gaṇhāhīti."
msgstr "saying, “Take as much as you like.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa755"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānenāti"
msgstr "If he wishes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "icchamānena."
msgstr "if he desires."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa756"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahetabbāti"
msgstr "He may accept two or three bowlfuls:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "dvetayo pattapūrā paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "two or three bowlfuls can be accepted."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa757"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "Tato ce uttari paṭigaṇheyyāti"
msgstr "If he accepts more than that:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "tatuttari paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he receives more than that, he commit an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa758"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "Dvattipattapūre paṭiggahetvā"
msgstr "If he accepts two or three bowlfuls:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "tato nikkhamantena bhikkhuṃ passitvā ācikkhitabbaṃ—"
msgstr "leaving that place and seeing a monk, he should tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid "“amutra mayā dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahitā, mā kho tattha paṭiggaṇhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I’ve accepted two or three bowlfuls from such-and-such a place; don’t "
"receive anything from there.”"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.21"
msgid "Sace passitvā na ācikkhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he sees a monk, but does not tell him, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

#. </span>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.22"
msgid "Sace ācikkhite paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If one who is told accepts from there regardless, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

#. </span></span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.81"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa759"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.325"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.23"
msgid "Tato nīharitvā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvibhajitabbanti"
msgstr "He should take it away and share it with the monks:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.24"
msgid "paṭikkamanaṃ nīharitvā saṃvibhajitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"he should take it away when he is returning from almsround and then share it."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa760"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.25"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr "This is the proper procedure:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs3.1.26"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "this is the right method."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.34.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa761"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Atirekadvattipattapūre atirekasaññī paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, and he perceives it as more, and "
"he receives it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Atirekadvattipattapūre vematiko paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, but he is unsure if it is, and he "
"receives it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Atirekadvattipattapūre ūnakasaññī paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, but he perceives it as less, and "
"he receives it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa762"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Ūnakadvattipattapūre atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, but he perceives it as more, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Ūnakadvattipattapūre vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, but he is unsure if it is, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Ūnakadvattipattapūre ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, and he perceives it as less, there "
"is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.34.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa763"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "dvattipattapūre paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he accepts two or three bowlfuls;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "ūnakadvattipattapūre paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he accepts less than two or three bowlfuls;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "na paheṇakatthāya na pātheyyatthāya paṭiyattaṃ denti,"
msgstr ""
"if they give anything that has not been prepared for sending away or for "
"provisions for a journey;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "paheṇakatthāya vā pātheyyatthāya vā paṭiyattasesakaṃ denti,"
msgstr ""
"if they give the leftovers from what was prepared for sending away or for "
"provisions for a journey;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "gamane paṭippassaddhe denti,"
msgstr "if they give after the plans to travel have been canceled;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "attano,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.10"
msgid "dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa764"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:pts-cs2.3.13"
msgid "Kāṇamātusikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on Kāṇamātā, is finished."

